risks_and_outlook.key_risks: Economic conditions, competition, regulation, financial markets, consumer spending patterns, debt levels, security breaches, and geopolitical conditions
risks_and_outlook.guidance: The Board of Directors has reauthorized a common stock repurchase program of up to $4 billion, which will expire in January 2027.
risks_and_outlook.market_conditions: Domestic and international economic conditions, including exchange rates, inflation or deflation, the effects of competition and regulation, uncertainties in the financial markets, consumer and small business spending patterns and debt levels
